\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 1.              Athyrium}               Roth
\par       

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By A.C. Jermy.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Rhizome branched, covered with broadly lanceolate, acuminate scales. Leaves uniform, forming a crown at apex of rhizome, 2-pinnate, with pinnatifid or pinnatisect pinnules; lamina broadly lanceolate with pinnae decreasing towards base; veins free. Sori oblong or orbicular; indusium rudimentary and caducous, or persistent, oblong or linear, fimbriate at margin, attached laterally, opening towards the midrib.
\par

