\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. A. filix-femina} (L.) Roth, {\i Tent. Fl. Germ.}{\b  3}({\b 1}): 65 (1799) ({\i Polypodium rhaeticum} L.,{\i  P. axillare} Aiton,{\i  Asplenium filix-femina} (L.) Bernh.). Rhizome short, suberect. Leaves 20-150 cm, suberect or spreading; petiole pale yellowish-green or purplish-red, ¼-½ as long as the lamina; lamina thin, flaccid, light green, lanceolate; longest pinnae 3-25 cm, decreasing towards base of leaf, linear-lanceolate, tapered at apex; pinnules 3-20 mm, sessile, oblong or oblong-lanceolate, pinnatifid or pinnatisect. Sori c. 1 mm, more or less oblong; indusium persistent, flap-like, the lower hooked, the upper nearly straight; spores minutely papillose. 2n = 80. {\i Shady places. Throughout Europe but local in the south and east.} All except Rs(K) Sb.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 This species has many variants, differing mainly in the form and dissection of the leaf, which bear no relation to habitat.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   {\b 2. A. distentifolium} Tausch ex Opiz, {\i Tent. Fl. Crypt. Boem. }{\b 1:} 14 (1820) ({\i A. alpestre} (Hoppe) Rylands ex T. Moore, non Clairv., {\i Polypodium rhaeticum }auct., non L.). Like {\b 1} but segments of pinnules usually blunt and often tricuspidate at apex; sori less than 1 mm, orbicular, near edge of lamina; indusium rudimentary or caducous at a very early stage; spores reticulate, with narrow wings. 2n = 80.{\i  Screes and rocky outcrops in exposed places. N. Europe; mountains of C. & S.Europe}. Au Br Bu Co Cz Fa Fe Ga Ge He Hs Is It Ju No Po Rm Rs(N, C, W) Su.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Var.{\i  flexile} (Newman) Jermy ({\i A. flexile} (Newman) Druce), known only from Scotland, has leaves 15-25 cm and very small sori, often of 3-5 sporangia only.
